 buying organizations, while others are forced to 
 accept the state's use of (written promises to pay) (IOU) 
 instead of cash for their products 9 . In many cases, 
 special fees have been charged and collected by local governments 
 on farmers that are related to purchase and input 
 supply. In these situations, the actual prices received 
 and paid by farmers are different from what has been 
 watched/followed in the market because of the existence of 
 these non-price restrictions. 
